 {"id":"brenner_bot-1es5.3","title":"Task: Implement CLI experiment encode (results → delta blocks)","description":"# Goal
Implement a deterministic CLI encoder that turns structured `ExperimentResult` JSON into mergeable, **non-interpretive** DELTA blocks.

---

# Proposed CLI surface (draft)
```bash
./brenner.ts experiment encode \
  --thread-id RS-... \
  --test-id T1 \
  --result-file artifacts/RS-.../results/T1_....json \
  --out-file deltas.md
```

- Output is a markdown message body containing `## Deltas` and one or more ```delta blocks.

---

# What this encoder does NOT do
- It does not decide “which hypothesis is correct”.
- It does not kill hypotheses automatically.

It only attaches run metadata + references to the artifact in a deterministic way.

---

# UX considerations
- Output should be directly suitable for `mail send`.
- Fail loudly when required metadata is missing.

---

# Acceptance criteria
- [ ] Encoder output parses via delta-parser
- [ ] Encoder output updates the intended test item deterministically
- [ ] Unit tests cover key cases (missing mapping, missing file, etc.)
